content.description: Travelers are increasingly using generative AI to plan trips.
UBS highlights ongoing economic concerns for FedEx and UPS.
Cruise line parent set to report earnings amid loyalty program backlash.
Social Security may stop sharing customer service performance data.
Analysts say Palantir could be overvalued despite defense-related growth potential. Maybe not if they keep getting government contracts however.
Markets remain resilient despite global conflict risks.

outlook: Travelers are turning to AI for trip planning while the cruise industry eyes earnings as loyalty changes stir backlash. (Could this be an issue for the travel industry?). Social Security transparency may decline, Palantir appears overpriced despite defense potential, and markets stay strong amid global tensions.
